  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Idiopathic PD

          -  Hoehn and Yahr stage I-III

          -  Between 40 and 75 years old

          -  Not meeting the norm for healthy physical activity: the latter being defined according
             to international standards as either five days a week 30 minutes of moderate-intensity
             physical activity, or 3 days a week 20 minutes of vigorous-intensity physical activity

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Wheel chair bounded

          -  Severe co-morbidity (e.g. orthopaedic disorders or chronic hart failure)

          -  Severe cognitive decline, defined as Mini Mental State Examination &lt; 24
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
